“ Cicero was above all things an Orator. To be the greatest orator of Rome, the equal of DemostheneS, was his supreme desire, and to it all other studies were made subservient. Poetry, history, law, philosophy, were regarded by him only as so many qualifications without which an orator could not be perfect. He could not conceive a great orator except as a great man, nor a good orator except as a good man.”
